First off, I think the listed changes are overkill. But some kind of nerf had to be coming.<br>
<br>
I'm not at the high end game, as I'm only 57. I don't play an enchanter nor know the difficulties of charm soloing. I do hdyra a cleric and warrior though, and their relative solo power in comparison to a solo charming enchanter in its current state is laughable.<br>
<br>
Why do I think charming needed to be nerfed? A 57 enchanter with 6 AAs (as in NONE that affect charm) who I religiously group with could charm a trash mob in PoI, haste it and get around 180 dps. I have no idea how that rates to charming other mobs in higher tiers, and a lot of people will probably laugh at that number.<br>
<br>
However, I do occasionaly group with a level 65 ranger who has all the fun AAs of a ranger and decent gear, as the guild is currently Vex Thal capable. The ranger averages around 120 dps against the same mobs (some of which are conning light blue).<br>
<br>
I'm not going to make any broad comments about enchanters charm soloing as I have no experience in that area. However, a 57 enchanter outdamaging a 65 ranger by 30% when all other factors like gear and AA aren't even comparable is unreasonable considering SOE's view of those class's respective roles. <br>
<br>
Yes, the risk is a bit higher when charming, but death in the planes is just a 20 minute inconvenience now as you wait for a graveyard pop, and we'll gladly exchange a good hour of chewing through mobs for that.<br>
<br>
I expect to be ripped apart for n00bishness because of the low dps numbers, but it is supposed to be a relative power example.<br>
<br>
Once again, the stated nerf changes above are overkill, but something was bound to come.<br>
<br>
